While there is no "official" downloadable offline course file, Wazuh provides extensive training materials and documentation for security engineers at no cost. 
Official Training & Materials
Wazuh Training Syllabus: The official Wazuh for Security Engineers syllabus is available for download as a PDF. It outlines a 4-day intensive structure covering architecture, log analysis, decoders, rulesets, and incident response.
Official Documentation: The Wazuh Documentation serves as the primary technical resource, including a Getting Started guide and detailed configuration manuals for all features.
Offline Installation Guide: For engineers working in air-gapped or restricted environments, Wazuh provides an offline installation guide to help set up the platform without an internet connection. 
Free Alternative Learning Platforms
Several reputable third-party platforms offer structured Wazuh courses for security engineers for free: 
TryHackMe: The Wazuh Room provides a hands-on, interactive environment to practice SIEM and EDR tasks.
LetsDefend: Offers a Wazuh training module covering installation, custom log parsing, and writing correlation rules.
YouTube Tutorials:
2-Hour+ Wazuh Crash Course specifically designed for security analysts.
Wazuh Tutorial for Beginners which includes demonstration of hacking techniques and detection. 
Quickstart Resources
All-in-one Installation: For rapid lab setup, use the Wazuh Quickstart, which installs the server, indexer, and dashboard on a single host.
GitHub Repository: Access the source code, community-contributed scripts, and additional tools directly on GitHub. 
